{300}{}{你是谁？ -- Who are you?}
### {301}{}{You cross a valley, you walk through a whole pueblo and you don't know who is in front of you? It's strong. Then let's take care of your upbringing - I'm the one whose name is Geronimo. I am the supreme leader of my entire tribe.}
{301}{}{你穿过一个山谷，穿过整个普韦布洛，却不知道谁在你面前？它很强壮。那么，让我们照顾好你的成长――我就是那个叫杰罗尼莫的人。我是整个部落的最高领袖。 -- You cross a valley, you walk through a whole pueblo and you don't know who is in front of you? It's strong. Then let's take care of your upbringing - I'm the one whose name is Geronimo. I am the supreme leader of my entire tribe.}
### {302}{}{Tell me about yourself, Chief.}
{302}{}{跟我说说你自己吧，警长。 -- Tell me about yourself, Chief.}
### {303}{}{Do you really have such a short memory? Then it's worth refreshing it a little - I'm the one whose name is Geronimo. I am the supreme leader of the tribe.}
{303}{}{你真的记性这么差吗？然后值得稍微刷新一下――我就是那个叫Geronimo的人。我是部落的最高领袖。 -- Do you really have such a short memory? Then it's worth refreshing it a little - I'm the one whose name is Geronimo. I am the supreme leader of the tribe.}
### {304}{}{Supreme? So there are others?}
{304}{}{最高的那么还有其他人吗？ -- Supreme? So there are others?}
### {305}{}{The tribe consists of clans, each clan has its own leader or representative. Together we unite for a time of severe trials. And the rest of the time we wander around Sonora in search of food.}
{305}{}{部落由氏族组成，每个氏族都有自己的首领或代表。我们团结在一起度过了一段严峻的考验时期。剩下的时间我们在索诺拉四处寻找食物。 -- The tribe consists of clans, each clan has its own leader or representative. Together we unite for a time of severe trials. And the rest of the time we wander around Sonora in search of food.}
### {306}{}{Now it became clear.}
{306}{}{现在它变得清晰起来。 -- Now it became clear.}

### {310}{}{Tell us about your people.}
{310}{}{告诉我们您的员工。 -- Tell us about your people.}
### {311}{}{Do you want to know the history of the tribe? We suffered a lot, but remained faithful to our roots.}
{311}{}{你想知道这个部落的历史吗？我们遭受了很多痛苦，但仍然忠于我们的根。 -- Do you want to know the history of the tribe? We suffered a lot, but remained faithful to our roots.}
### {312}{}{Sorry, Chief, but I don't have time to listen to long stories right now.}
{312}{}{对不起，警长，我现在没有时间听长篇故事。 -- Sorry, Chief, but I don't have time to listen to long stories right now.}
### {313}{}{That's it, the young no longer want to know history and honor their ancestors. And that bothers me.}
{313}{}{就是这样，年轻人不再想了解历史和尊敬他们的祖先。这让我很困扰。 -- That's it, the young no longer want to know history and honor their ancestors. And that bothers me.}
### {314}{}{Some other time.}
{314}{}{改天吧。 -- Some other time.}
### {315}{}{Tell me more.}
{315}{}{告诉我更多。 -- Tell me more.}
### {316}{}{We have been living in the lands of Sonora for many generations. Our ancestors lived here even before the world fell from the wrath of the Fiery Brahmin.}
{316}{}{我们在索诺拉的土地上生活了好几代人。我们的祖先甚至在世界从愤怒的婆罗门的愤怒中堕落之前就住在这里。 -- We have been living in the lands of Sonora for many generations. Our ancestors lived here even before the world fell from the wrath of the Fiery Brahmin.}
### {317}{}{It's hard to believe that you were able to survive in the desert for so long.}
{317}{}{很难相信你能在沙漠中生存这么长时间。 -- It's hard to believe that you were able to survive in the desert for so long.}
### {318}{}{It's a miracle that you managed to survive the War.}
{318}{}{你能在战争中幸存下来真是个奇迹。 -- It's a miracle that you managed to survive the War.}
### {319}{}{For a long time, the tribe consisted of many small families scattered throughout the desert. Everyone survived as best they could. The infirm and sick died out, and the strong and healthy continued their kind. When the families multiplied and there was not enough land for everyone, clan wars began.}
{319}{}{很长一段时间以来，这个部落由许多分散在沙漠中的小家庭组成。每个人都尽力活了下来。体弱多病的人死了，强壮健康的人继续他们的同类。当家族繁衍，没有足够的土地容纳每个人时，部族战争就开始了。 -- For a long time, the tribe consisted of many small families scattered throughout the desert. Everyone survived as best they could. The infirm and sick died out, and the strong and healthy continued their kind. When the families multiplied and there was not enough land for everyone, clan wars began.}
### {320}{}{Is there no war between the clans now?}
{320}{}{现在部族之间没有战争了吗？ -- Is there no war between the clans now?}
### {321}{}{The threat to the Phoenix Empire forced us to unite. The townspeople began to steal our cattle, traders began to cheat, slavers appeared in our lands. We couldn't take it anymore.}
{321}{}{对凤凰帝国的威胁迫使我们团结起来。镇上的人开始偷我们的牛，商人开始作弊，奴隶贩子出现在我们的土地上。我们再也受不了了。 -- The threat to the Phoenix Empire forced us to unite. The townspeople began to steal our cattle, traders began to cheat, slavers appeared in our lands. We couldn't take it anymore.}
### {322}{}{What did you do?}
{322}{}{你做了什么？ -- What did you do?}
### {323}{}{The elders gathered around a common fire and decided to unite. I was one of those who reconciled and gathered the tribe. It happened here, within the walls of an ancient pueblo.}
{323}{}{长老们聚集在一堆篝火旁，决定团结起来。我是和解并召集部落的人之一。它发生在这里，在一个古老的普韦布洛人的墙内。 -- The elders gathered around a common fire and decided to unite. I was one of those who reconciled and gathered the tribe. It happened here, within the walls of an ancient pueblo.}
### {324}{}{Thanks for the story. See you again, Geronimo.}
{324}{}{谢谢你的故事。再见，杰罗尼莫。 -- Thanks for the story. See you again, Geronimo.}
### {325}{}{An inspiring story. Let me ask you about other things.}
{325}{}{一个鼓舞人心的故事。让我问你其他事情。 -- An inspiring story. Let me ask you about other things.}
### {326}{}{No, I just want to talk about another topic.}
{326}{}{不，我只是想谈另一个话题。 -- No, I just want to talk about another topic.}

### {330}{}{You said you knew me. From where? }
{330}{}{你说你认识我，从哪里来的？ -- You said you knew me. From where? }
### {331}{}{Not you, but your father. I've met him before. A strong man. Persistent. One that everyone respects.}
{331}{}{不是你，而是你父亲。我以前见过他。一个坚强的人。坚持不懈。每个人都尊敬的人。 -- Not you, but your father. I've met him before. A strong man. Persistent. One that everyone respects.}
### {332}{}{Oh, yes, he is.}
{332}{}{哦，是的，他是。 -- Oh, yes, he is.}
### {333}{}{My padre is not worth such words. He could not resist the invaders and surrendered.}
{333}{}{我的牧师不值得这样说。他无法抵抗侵略者而投降了。 -- My padre is not worth such words. He could not resist the invaders and surrendered.}
### {334}{}{But he made it clear that he did not want a stranger to set foot in the Villa. We have concluded an isolation agreement. However, our tribe does not happen in those parts anyway. There's too little grass for cattle.}
{334}{}{但他明确表示，他不希望一个陌生人踏入别墅。我们达成了一项隔离协议。然而，我们的部落无论如何都不会发生在那些地方。草太少，不能放牛。 -- But he made it clear that he did not want a stranger to set foot in the Villa. We have concluded an isolation agreement. However, our tribe does not happen in those parts anyway. There's too little grass for cattle.}
### {335}{}{There's nothing but desert all around.}
{335}{}{周围除了沙漠什么都没有。 -- There's nothing but desert all around.}
### {336}{}{It is all the more amazing that you are growing a crop in the middle of barren soil. It was as if the Divine Brahmin himself kept your lands... until recently. Maybe you angered him with something?}
{336}{}{更令人惊讶的是，你在贫瘠的土壤中种植作物。就好像神圣的婆罗门自己保护了你的土地...直到最近。也许你用什么激怒了他？ -- It is all the more amazing that you are growing a crop in the middle of barren soil. It was as if the Divine Brahmin himself kept your lands... until recently. Maybe you angered him with something?}
### {337}{}{It is also interesting how such a miracle arose. But enough about my village. Shall we talk about yours?}
{337}{}{同样有趣的是，这样的奇迹是如何产生的。但我的村庄已经足够了。我们谈谈你的好吗？ -- It is also interesting how such a miracle arose. But enough about my village. Shall we talk about yours?}
### {338}{}{I don't think so. We just lost our vigilance. And by the way, it's time for me to hit the road, to correct this stupid mistake. See you later, Chief.}
{338}{}{我不这么认为。我们只是失去了警惕。顺便说一句，是时候让我上路了，纠正这个愚蠢的错误。回头见，长官。 -- I don't think so. We just lost our vigilance. And by the way, it's time for me to hit the road, to correct this stupid mistake. See you later, Chief.}

### {340}{}{I know you have an ancient book, Chief. Give it to me in a good way.}
{340}{}{我知道你有一本古书，首领。给我一个好的方式。 -- I know you have an ancient book, Chief. Give it to me in a good way.}
### {341}{}{A book? What are you talking about? We don't read any books.}
{341}{}{一本书？你在说什么？我们不读书。 -- A book? What are you talking about? We don't read any books.}
### {342}{}{You're lying. The Cathedral's book keeper could not be mistaken.}
{342}{}{你在撒谎。大教堂的簿记员不会弄错的。 -- You're lying. The Cathedral's book keeper could not be mistaken.}
### {343}{}{Please, people outside your tribe need this book.}
{343}{}{求你了，你部落以外的人需要这本书。 -- Please, people outside your tribe need this book.}
### {344}{}{Hmm, you must be talking about one of those old things that are stored in underground galleries.}
{344}{}{嗯，你一定是在说那些存放在地下画廊里的旧物。 -- Hmm, you must be talking about one of those old things that are stored in underground galleries.}
### {345}{}{Underground galleries? What are you talking about?}
{345}{}{地下画廊？你在说什么？ -- Underground galleries? What are you talking about?}
### {346}{}{You see, this ancient building has several floors buried by a layer of sand. There are still old things downstairs, but we don't need them. Therefore, no one goes down there and no one remembers what is there and what is not. And this is not the only buried place - the whole district has gone into the sand for several generations.}
{346}{}{你看，这座古老的建筑有几层被一层沙子掩埋。楼下还有旧东西，但我们不需要了。因此，没有人去那里，也没有人记得那里有什么，没有什么。这并不是唯一被埋葬的地方――整个地区已经被沙子掩埋了好几代人。 -- You see, this ancient building has several floors buried by a layer of sand. There are still old things downstairs, but we don't need them. Therefore, no one goes down there and no one remembers what is there and what is not. And this is not the only buried place - the whole district has gone into the sand for several generations.}
### {347}{}{So can I come down and get them?}
{347}{}{我能下来拿吗？ -- So can I come down and get them?}
### {348}{}{Try. But prepare for the worst. A spirit test awaits you below. I myself have heard the voices of long-dead people there. You may never get out of these ancient chambers, like other treasure hunters who went down there in search of relics.}
{348}{}{尝试但要做好最坏的打算。下面有一场精神测试等着你。我自己也听到了那里死去已久的人们的声音。你可能永远无法走出这些古老的洞穴，就像其他去那里寻找遗迹的寻宝者一样。 -- Try. But prepare for the worst. A spirit test awaits you below. I myself have heard the voices of long-dead people there. You may never get out of these ancient chambers, like other treasure hunters who went down there in search of relics.}
### {349}{}{I'll still take a chance. See you later, Chief.}
{349}{}{我还是要碰碰运气。回头见，长官。 -- I'll still take a chance. See you later, Chief.}
